 <item> <title>Default Rates Continue to Rise for Federal Student Loans</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/default-rates-continue-rise-federal-student-loans</link>
 <description>The U.S. Department of Education today announced the official FY 2011 two-year and official FY 2010 three-year federal student loan cohort default rates (CDR). The national two-year cohort default rate rose from 9.1 percent for FY 2010 to 10 percent for FY 2011. The three-year cohort default rate rose from 13.4 percent for FY 2009 to 14.7 percent for FY 2010.</description>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/default-rates-continue-rise-federal-student-loans</guid>
